The Emir of Karaye in Kano State, Alhaji Ibrahim Abubakar II, has directed Imams in the emirate to offer special prayers for rainfall and peace. The emir gave the directive on Wednesday, through the emirate Information Officer, Haruna Gunduwawa, in a statement. He directed all district and village heads to liaise with clerics in organising prayers in their respective areas. “You should dwell on praying to the Almighty Allah to provide us with rainfall in order to have bumper harvests and peace in the area,” he said. The emir also called on the clerics to pray to Allah to bring an end to COVID-19 pandemic. (NAN)